    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.24/145a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8.… has submitted to the Department an application for license to export to the
                    Government of Honduras 280,000 thirty-eight caliber <pb facs="0706" n="586"
                        xml:id="pg_586"/> cartridges and 120,000 thirty-two caliber cartridges.
                    Because of the calibers specified the Department desires you to ascertain and
                    report by telegraph whether this material would be imported strictly for
                    Government use.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
